{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require audio recordings of supervised contact sessions in family court",
        "additional_details": "Families may often rely on written notes that can affect court outcomes and their children\u2019s futures. Recordings could improve transparency, accuracy, accountability and fairness, reduce disputes, and protect children and vulnerable families. We believe parents and carers should be allowed to make recordings, with safeguards for confidentiality and welfare.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to require audio recordings of supervised family contact sessions, including social work interviews and safeguarding meetings, to be played in family court proceedings.",
